info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 23 at 2:00PM CST until February 24 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO 9 AM CST FRIDAY... ...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IS CANCELLED... * WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low as 30 below zero. * WHERE...Central St. Louis, Southern Lake, North Cass, South Itasca and Northern Aitkin Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Bois Forte Band, Lake Vermilion area and the Mille Lacs Band, Big Sandy Lake area. * WHEN...From 3 AM to 9 AM CST Friday. * IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
info.instruction: Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and gloves.
